         <div>
            <head>Translated parts</head>
            <p xml:id="KR6q0003-start">
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_010-0274a.60" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2019-10-18T11:45:25.084+09:00">Ein Mönch fragte</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_010-0274a.61" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2019-10-18T11:46:58.875+09:00">"In den Schriften</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_010-0274a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2019-10-18T11:46:59.345+09:00">wird häufig von einem 'Bodhisattva Sitz' gesprochen.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_010-0274a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2019-10-18T11:46:59.802+09:00">Was hat es damit auf sich?"</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_010-0274a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2019-10-18T11:46:55.5+09:00">                                    Changsha antwortete:</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_017-0337b.58" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2020-03-06T13:26:53.307+09:00">das wird es dir erzählen."</seg>
            <seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:14.611+09:00">All the Buddhas and all sentient beings</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:15.601+09:00">are nothing but the One Mind,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.64" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:20.678+09:00">beside which nothing exists.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.65" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:47.384+09:00">This Mind, which is without beginning,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:48.091+09:00">is unborn and indestructible.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.67" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:19:49.733+09:00">It is not green nor yellow,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.68" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:20:13.654+09:00">and has neither form nor appearance.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.69" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:20:18.913+09:00">It does not belong to the categories of things which exist or do not exist,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.70" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:20:27.25+09:00">nor can it be thought of in terms of new or old.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.71" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:20:52.032+09:00">It is neither long nor short,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.72" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:20:55.272+09:00">big nor small,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.73" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:21:13.283+09:00">for it transcends all limits, measures, names, traces and comparisons.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.74" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:22:11.52+09:00">It is that which you see before you—</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.75" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:22:14.004+09:00">begin to reason about it and you at once fall into error.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.76" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:23:33.994+09:00">It is like the  void</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.77" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:23:24.836+09:00">which has no boundaries</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.78" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:23:27.259+09:00">and can not be fathomed or measured.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.79" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:24:26.642+09:00">This One Mind alone is the Buddha,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.80" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:24:56.626+09:00">and between the Buddha and sentient things,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.81" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:24:57.745+09:00">there is no distinction</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.82" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:28:20.602+09:00">but that sentient beings are attached to forms</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.83" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:28:21.532+09:00">and so  seek externally [for Buddhahood]. By their very seeking they lose it,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.84" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:28:22.661+09:00">for that is using the Buddha to seek for the Buddha and</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.85" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:28:23.334+09:00">using mind to grasp Mind.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.86" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:30:30.55+09:00">Even though they do their utmost for a full aeon,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.87" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:30:31.385+09:00">they will not be able to attain to it.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.88" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:30:51.096+09:00">They do not know that, if they put a stop to conceptual thought and forget their anxiety,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.89" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:30:52.205+09:00">the Buddha will appear before them,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.90" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:37:39.791+09:00">for this Mind is the Buddha</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.91" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:37:41.495+09:00">and the Buddha is all living beings.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.92" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:37:47.558+09:00">The living beings are Buddha</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270b.93" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:37:53.723+09:00">and Buddha is this Mind.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270c.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:39:15.903+09:00">for being manifested in ordinary beings</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270c.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:39:17.198+09:00">It is not the less ,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270c.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:39:19.823+09:00">for being manifested in the Buddhas.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6q0003_T_009-0270c.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-01-03T10:39:29.823+09:00"> it is not greater.</seg></p>
         </div>
